==English==
===Etymology===
Sanskrit [[सत्गुरू]] ''satgurū'' (sat=true; guru=teacher)

===Noun===
'''satguru'''
#In Hinduism and Buddhism, a great [[teacher]]; a supremely wise guide.
#In Sikhism, one of many names for [[God]].

